			 Always Encrypted (Database Engine) 

					 
								 04/24/2017 
							 13 minutes to read 
							 
								 Contributors 
								 
											 
											 
											 
											 
								 

					 In this article 
						 THIS TOPIC APPLIES TO:   SQL Server Azure SQL Database Azure SQL Data Warehouse  Parallel Data Warehouse     
  Always Encrypted is a feature designed to protect sensitive data, such as credit card numbers or national identification numbers (for example, U.S. social security numbers), stored in  Azure SQL Database or  SQL Server databases. Always Encrypted allows clients to encrypt sensitive data inside client applications and never reveal the encryption keys to the  Database Engine ( SQL Database or  SQL Server). As a result, Always Encrypted provides a separation between those who own the data (and can view it) and those who manage the data (but shou